               <p>WALTER BERDOE. I was on <placeName id="t18300916-285-crimeloc1450">Clerkenwell-green</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-285-crimeloc1450" type="placeName" value="Clerkenwell-green"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-285-crimeloc1450" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-285-off1448 t18300916-285-crimeloc1450"></join>, between four and five o'clock, on the 14th of September - I was standing opposite the booth at the election, and felt a hand gently withdrawing itself from my pocket; I turned, and saw the prisoner - he said, "It was not me that did it;" the handkerchiefs was on the ground - there was a mob there: I took him, and gave charge of him - two other silk handkerchiefs were found next his skin, and the duplicate of another.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Can you swear I took it? A. To the best of my belief you did, because no other person, I think, could have taken it, and dropped it there.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. It is a matter of impossibility for him to swear I did it; I was unfortunately next to him - he turned, and asked a gentleman if he saw me do it; the gentleman said No; he said, I did, and took me.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18300916-285-verdict1451" type="verdictDescription">
